**7. Octal and Hexadecimal Number Systems**

Both Octal (Base 8) and Hexadecimal (Base 16) are used to make **long binary strings shorter and easier for humans** to read.

** 7.1 Why do we group binary?

| System | Grouping Rule | Reason |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Octal** | Group binary digits into **groups of 3** (bits) | 2³ = 8, so one octal digit = 3 binary digits. |
| **Hexadecimal** | Group binary digits into **groups of 4** (bits) | 2⁴ = 16, so one hex digit = 4 binary digits. |

---

**7.2 Converting Binary to Octal (Group of 3)**

**Example:** Convert `(101101)₂` to Octal.

| Step | Action | Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 1 | Write the binary number | 101101 |
| 2 | Group from right to left into 3s | 101  101 |
| 3 | Convert each group to decimal (0-7) | 101 = 5,  101 = 5 |

**Answer:** (101101)₂ = **(55)₈**

---

**7.3 Converting Binary to Hexadecimal (Group of 4)**

**Example:** Convert `(101101)₂` to Hexadecimal.

| Step | Action | Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 1 | Write the binary number | 101101 |
| 2 | Add leading zeros to make a group of 4 | 0010  1101 (Added two zeros on left) |
| 3 | Convert each group to decimal (0-15) | 0010 = 2,  1101 = 13 (which is D in Hex) |

**Answer:** (101101)₂ = **(2D)₁₆**

---

**📊 Binary to Octal/Hex Grouping**

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Binary Number
        B[1 0 1 1 0 1]
    end
    
    B --> O[Group into 3s for Octal]
    B --> H[Group into 4s for Hex]
    
    O --> O1[101 101]
    O1 --> O2[5 5]
    O2 --> O3[Octal = 55]
    
    H --> H1[0010 1101]
    H1 --> H2["2 13 (D)"]
    H2 --> H3[Hexadecimal = 2D]
    
    style B fill:#f9f,stroke:#333
    style O3 fill:#9cf,stroke:#333
    style H3 fill:#9cf,stroke:#333
```

---

**7.4 Converting Octal/Hex to Decimal (Quick Recap)**

You can always convert Octal or Hexadecimal to decimal using the place-value method.

**Octal Example:** (325)₈  
= (3 × 8²) + (2 × 8¹) + (5 × 8⁰)  
= (3 × 64) + (2 × 8) + (5 × 1)  
= 192 + 16 + 5 = **(213)₁₀**

**Hex Example:** (2F)₁₆  
= (2 × 16¹) + (15 × 16⁰)  *(Since F = 15)*  
= 32 + 15 = **(47)₁₀**

